<tmc-service-paragraph><pub id="RM25T0E"><servcat id="_51"><name>Engine / Hybrid System</name><section id="_029760"><name>1VD-FTV ENGINE CONTROL</name><ttl id="_0135360"><name>ECD SYSTEM</name><para category="C" id="RM100000000FJJN"><dtccode>P0405</dtccode><dtcname>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor "A" Circuit Low</dtcname><dtccode>P0406</dtccode><dtcname>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor "A" Circuit High</dtcname><dtccode>P0407</dtccode><dtcname>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor "B" Circuit Low</dtcname><dtccode>P0408</dtccode><dtcname>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor "B" Circuit High</dtcname><subpara category="03" id="RM100000000FJJN_01"><name>DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>The EGR valve position sensor is mounted on the EGR valve and used for detecting the lift amount of the valve. The lift amount detected by the sensor is provided to the ECM as feedback. The ECM then regulates the lift amount of the valve in accordance with engine running conditions.</ptxt><table pgwide="1" type="dtc-explan-table"><tgroup cols="6"><colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.42in"/><colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="4" colwidth="1.77in"/><colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/><colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.70in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC No.</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Detection Item</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>DTC Detection Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Trouble Area</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>MIL</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Memory</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0405</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor "A" Circuit Low</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>No. 1 EGR valve position sensor output voltage is less than 0.1 V for more than 5 seconds</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Open or short in No. 1 EGR valve position sensor circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>No. 1 EGR valve (EGR valve position sensor)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0406</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor "A" Circuit High</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>No. 1 EGR valve position sensor output voltage is more than 4.9 V for more than 5 seconds</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Open or short in No. 1 EGR valve position sensor circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>No. 1 EGR valve (EGR valve position sensor)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0407</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor "B" Circuit Low</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>No. 2 EGR valve position sensor output voltage is less than 0.1 V for more than 5 seconds</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Open or short in No. 2 EGR valve position sensor circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>No. 2 EGR valve (EGR valve position sensor)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row><row><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-code"><ptxt>P0408</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="detect-item"><ptxt>Exhaust Gas Recirculation Sensor "B" Circuit High</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="dtc-detect-cond"><ptxt>No. 2 EGR valve position sensor output voltage is more than 4.9 V for more than 5 seconds</ptxt><ptxt>(1 trip detection logic)</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="trouble-area"><list1 type="unordered"><item><ptxt>Open or short in No. 2 EGR valve position sensor circuit</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>No. 2 EGR valve (EGR valve position sensor)</ptxt></item><item><ptxt>ECM</ptxt></item></list1></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="mil"><ptxt>Comes on</ptxt></data-name></entry><entry align="left" valign="middle"><data-name name="memory"><ptxt>DTC stored</ptxt></data-name></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></content5></subpara><subpara category="03" id="RM100000000FJJN_02"><name>MONITOR DESCRIPTION</name><content5><ptxt>When the output voltage of the EGR valve position sensor deviates from the normal operating range of 0.1 to 4.9 V for more than 0.5 seconds, the ECM interprets this as a malfunction of the sensor circuit, and illuminates the MIL.</ptxt></content5></subpara><subpara category="03" id="RM100000000FJJN_03"><name>WIRING DIAGRAM</name><content5><ptxt>Refer to DTC P0400.</ptxt><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref href="RM100000000FJK0_03" label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001"/></mlink></ptxt></content5></subpara><subpara category="10" id="RM100000000FJJN_04"><name>CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT</name><content5><atten3><ptxt>After replacing the ECM, the new ECM needs registration (See page <mlink><xref href="RM100000000FJKB" label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001"/></mlink>) and initialization (See page <mlink><xref href="RM100000000FJIX" label="Seep00002" term-id-from="001"/></mlink>).</ptxt></atten3><atten4><ptxt>Read freeze frame data using the GTS. Freeze frame data records the engine condition when malfunctions are detected. When troubleshooting, freeze frame data can help determine if the vehicle was moving or stationary, if the engine was warmed up or not, and other data from the time the malfunction occurred.</ptxt></atten4></content5></subpara><subpara category="01" id="RM100000000FJJN_06"><name>PROCEDURE</name><testgrp cellposition="1-1" id="RM100000000FJJN_06_0007"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (EGR VALVE POWER SOURCE)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the C47 or C66 EGR valve connector.</ptxt><figure translate="C" type="1"><graphic graphicname="A165766C04" height="3.434793307in" width="3.434793307in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*1</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>No. 1</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*2</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>No. 2</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Front view of wire harness connector</ptxt><ptxt>(to EGR Valve)</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the voltage according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard voltage</title><table><title>No. 1</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Switch Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C47-3 (VC) - C47-2 (E2)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Ignition switch ON</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>4.5 to 5.5 V</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><table><title>No. 2</title><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Switch Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>C66-3 (VC) - C66-2 (E2)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Ignition switch ON</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>4.5 to 5.5 V</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result cellposition="1-1" label="1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="2-1" childid="RM100000000FJJN_06_0001"/></result><result cellposition="1-4" label="2"><action actiontype="jump" cellposition="2-4" childid="RM100000000FJJN_06_0006"><actiontitle>GO TO STEP 3</actiontitle></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp cellposition="2-1" id="RM100000000FJJN_06_0001"><testtitle>INSPECT EGR VALVE ASSEMBLY (NO. 1 OR NO. 2) (POSITION SENSOR)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the C47 or C66 EGR valve connector.</ptxt><figure translate="C" type="1"><graphic graphicname="A165764C02" height="3.434793307in" width="3.434793307in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Component without harness connected</ptxt><ptxt>(EGR Valve)</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></callout></figure></test1><test1><ptxt>Measure the resistance according to the value(s) in the table below.</ptxt><spec type="other"><title>Standard resistance</title><table><tgroup cols="3"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1.38in"/><colspec colname="col3" colwidth="1.37in"/><thead><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Tester Connection</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Condition</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Specified Condition</ptxt></entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>3 (VC) - 2 (E2)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>20°C (68°F)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>2.45 to 4.55 kΩ</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>4 (EGLS) - 2 (E2)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>20°C (68°F)</ptxt></entry><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>2.45 to 4.55 kΩ</ptxt></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></test1><spec type="other"><title>Result</title><table><tgroup cols="1"><colspec colname="col1" colwidth="4.13in"/><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="1"><ptxt>OK</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><judge-value label="2"><ptxt>NG</ptxt></judge-value></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></spec></content6><results><result cellposition="2-1" label="1"><action actiontype="next" cellposition="3-1" childid="RM100000000FJJN_06_0006"/></result><result cellposition="2-3" label="2"><action actiontype="end" cellposition="3-3"><actiontitle>REPLACE EGR VALVE ASSEMBLY (NO. 1 OR NO. 2)</actiontitle><content6><ptxt>Click here<mlink><xref href="RM100000000FDIB" label="Seep00001" term-id-from="001"/></mlink></ptxt></content6></action></result></results></testgrp><testgrp cellposition="3-1" id="RM100000000FJJN_06_0006"><testtitle>CHECK HARNESS AND CONNECTOR (EGR VALVE - ECM)</testtitle><content6><test1><ptxt>Disconnect the C47 or C66 EGR valve connector.</ptxt><figure translate="C" type="1"><graphic graphicname="A311467C04" height="4.677165354in" width="3.434793307in"/><callout><table pgwide="0" type="caption-table"><tgroup cols="2"><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="0.69in"/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.75in"/><tbody><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*1</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>No. 1</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*2</ptxt></entry><entry><ptxt>No. 2</ptxt></entry></row><row><entry align="center" valign="middle"><ptxt>*a</ptxt></entry><entry valign="middle"><ptxt>Front view of wire harness connector</ptxt><ptxt>(to EGR Valve)</ptxt></entry></row><row><entr